The paper deals with medical image classification using deep learning techniques, specifically for chest X-rays. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a novel error function to address the properties of multiple labels and imbalanced data, which involves machine learning techniques such as transfer learning and fine-grained classification. This could potentially fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on various network backbones, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) techniques. Finally, the paper deals with medical image retrieval, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
